<pictures>None< /pictures><Rating>4< /Rating><Response>None</Response><Time>1588812344305</Time>< user_name>
Christopher Hyun< /user_name>
< Review>
Barstow, Calif.
Mojave river museum is small, local joint. Main showcases are local flair.
Highlights are the high school accomplishments, couple locals, african american role in the city and bunch of nature things like rocks and wildlife.

Native american roots are also highlighted.

This museum has a variety of things explaining how or what barstow was except for a pitstop for the trains or travelers heading to or away from los angeles.

The museum feels a bit cluttered and is good for kids.

Location: A
Right off the I-15 Freeway.
Mojave museum is on the Southwest corner of Barstow & E Virginia.

Roads/Parking: A
Plenty parking on rough road.

Cost: A
Free.

Overall: A
Nothing to travel thousands of miles for. Ideal if your commuting to/from vegas or to/from grand canyons to so cal.

Notable nearbys:
Down the street located at the Harvey House are Rte 66 Museum, Train museum and planet exhibition.
Back way to Big Bear, Morongo/Palm Springs and Fort Irwin.
Nearby on the same street is the Discovery/Geology Museum and Historic DT Barstow where Roy's cafe and bunch of Rte 66 signs are.
Barstow also has a huge outlets that is famous for Asian tourists.

Safe traveling.
@cigarcpa.</Review>

<Rate>5<//Rate>< Text>
I just don't get why anyone would by a tire anywhere else. The service is always so great, and yet the prices are always the lowest (The sign next door at Evans Tires that says "we beat discount is 100% BS). Discount even beats Costco on price. And it beats the F out of Evans and anyone else from head to toe.

I've been had dealings with probably about 10 of the locations over the years. This store is typical Discount Tire - customer service above all else. This last stop was my third at this location. I lease cars for a year at a time now, and no longer buy tires for myself. I do buy tires for my kids regularly.

Yesterday, I stopped in to have a new tire fixed. Not a new tire I bought from Discount, but one on a relatively new car. I wasn't asked if I bought the tire there, and they did not know me from previous business I had done with Discount. They fixed my tire for free, checked and adjusted the tire pressure in the other three, and had me on my way in 30 minutes. Why? Because that's what Discount Tire does. No upsell, no pitch, just a smile and when I asked why it was free, the response was "we can't have people driving on dangerous tires" :)

So two messages:

1) You're crazy if you buy tires anywhere else. Costco somewhat excepted, but you won't get this kind of service. That only applies to tires btw, Costco rocks.

2) FY Evans Tires. There is no measurable value you beat Discount at anything. Not even price, which is the insinuation. But you did rip my son off one time very cleverly!</Text>
